Patch Set 2:

(1 comment)

Nikhil, since an image when created, first goes to ``queued`` state, the functional tests depend on allowing location updates on a queued image. https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/tests/functional/v2/test_images.py#L2829-L2863.
Also, there are other functional test cases like [1] that update an image location of a queued image to test another functionality.
If we are to not allow location updates at all for the queued images, we would have to change a lot of functional test cases.
[1] https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/tests/functional/v2/test_images.py#L3184
Wanted to make sure this is what we want and was hoping to get some advise here on how to proceed.

Patch Set 2:

> (1 comment)
 > 
 > Nikhil, since an image when created, first goes to ``queued``
 > state, the functional tests depend on allowing location updates on
 > a queued image. https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/tests/functional/v2/test_images.py#L2829-L2863.
 > Also, there are other functional test cases like [1] that update an
 > image location of a queued image to test another functionality.
 > If we are to not allow location updates at all for the queued
 > images, we would have to change a lot of functional test cases.
 > [1] https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/tests/functional/v2/test_images.py#L3184
 > Wanted to make sure this is what we want and was hoping to get some
 > advise here on how to proceed.

 	
Dharini, being able to update a location for a queued image is fundamentally wrong. At least, it is wrong, when we assume that updating is for replacing locations that exists. I think we may be using the update call in a wrong way -- i.e. to update the image with locations even when locations do not exist. So, it's not really an update to a location, rather update to the image which doesn't have location.

Assuming to "update locations" for a queued image is wrong as by definition a queued image is simply image record without any associated data. So, either location exists on the image or it's queued both can't be true (which is the case for the unit tests).

So, this needs further discussion with API_WG on how we'd proceed with such loosely coupled updates where location doesn't exist (empty) but we allow updates (which are in practice creates).

Given all of this, we may not be able to get it done in time for RC1 (let's see if we can for RC2). I will encourage you to keep working on it and we can bring it up in the glance meeting this Thursday.

Patch Set 2:

Thanks Nikhil and wangxiyuan

I agree that if ``replace`` means replacing an "empty" location to a "non-empty" location, "queued" image's location update may be permitted. But that will also mean we are opening way to replacing a non-empty location to an empty location and non-empty to another non-empty location.
We can add conditional statements though to check for the current location and depending on that permit replacing operation. 
Will continue working on this until we can talk about it in the glance meeting.
